# Architecture plan for Issue #123: Remove the per-message faction label from chat messages

## Project/module structure
- `frontend/src/App.tsx` renders the unified chat feed. The per-message faction label is currently a `<span className="tlhn-chat-faction">` inside each message's metadata row.
- `frontend/src/styles.css` contains the matching `.tlhn-chat-faction` style rule. That rule should be deleted once the markup is removed.
- `shared/src/*`, `backend/src/*`, database migrations, and API models remain unchanged because message payloads still include faction data for avatar/name coloring and accessibility.

## Issue dependencies and sequencing
- Issue #123 has no blocking dependencies.
- The implementation should be isolated to the unified chat feed UI and its unused CSS cleanup.

## Key design decisions
- Remove only the visible per-message faction text (`AI Haters` / `AI Lovers`) from chat message metadata.
- Preserve faction-colored display names, faction avatars, and the avatar `aria-label` exactly as requested.
- Keep message fetching, posting, ordering, history loading, timestamps, and shared faction types unchanged.
- Validate with the existing frontend/typecheck/build workflow after implementation.
